					<div class="media-body">
						<h4 class="media-heading"><a id="PositionSeniorAppSec">Open Position: Senior Application Security Consultant</a></h4>			
<!-- start content --			
<p>	Security PS is actively seeking out an experienced application security specialist to join our team as a Senior Security Consultant. Once established on the team, the senior consultant will lead application security engagements including activities such as:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Application Penetration Testing 
(Web Applications, Thick-Clients, Web Services, Mobile Applications, and more)
	<li>Threat Modeling
	<li>Architecture and Design Reviews
	<li>Code Reviews
	<li>Writing Secure Coding Patterns
	<li>Training Developers
	<li>Developing and Delivering Custom Consulting Solutions
</ul>

<p>Team members are also given the opportunity to cross-train and participate in network penetration testing and enterprise security engagements as a part of their ongoing professional development.</p>

<p>On our team, Senior members provide leadership on the team by developing other consultants, creating new offerings or services, providing oversight for others’ projects, as well as provide consulting expertise in their areas of research. All consultants interact directly with clients and are responsible for writing detailed documentation, therefore it is imperative that candidates excel at written and verbal communication.  </p>

<p>Our expectation is that a person well suited for this role would have the industry experience necessary for the position and would undergo a 4-6 month training period to learn and become proficient with our engagement and testing methodologies.</p>

<p>Security PS invests in the training and professional development of each team member. For the right candidate, we may consider a person for this position who demonstrates the capability but is currently lacking some areas of experience required to prove qualification. In this case, we would provide a longer training period with targeted professional development goals for achieving the qualifications and experience required for a senior consultant.
</p>

<h5 class="media-heading">Summary:</h5>
	<ul>
		<li>Focus: Application Security Consulting, Leadership, and Research </li>
		<li>Location: Kansas City metro area (local team, virtual office) </li>
		<li>Type: Full Time Employee</li>
		<li>Annual Salary: $100k + <i>(dependent on amount of experience and level of training necessary)</i></li>
		<li>Travel Profile: Low travel</li>
		<li>Qualifications Summary:</li>
		<ul>
			<li>Application Security penetration testing experience</li>
			<li>Software development experience and understanding of secure development practices</li>
			<li>Solid understanding of application technologies and platforms</li>
			<li>Ability to lead among peers when given the opportunity</li>
			<li>Proficient with the consulting process, including client communication and delivery</li>
			<li>Excellent soft skills (communication, writing, presenting)</li>
			<li>Effective time management, places personal value on hitting deadlines</li>
			<li>Motivated, productive worker, ability to work effectively from home / virtual office environment</li>
			<li>Valuable team member: supports, contributes, collaborates with others well</li>
		</ul>
		<li>Great Benefits, Including:</li>
