					<div class="media-body">
						<h4 class="media-heading"><a id="PositionAppSec">Open Position: Application Security Consultant</a></h4>			
<!-- start content -- 			
<p>Are you a software developer who is looking for a chance to work full-time in application security? Or maybe you’re already doing some application security work but would like a place to give you the challenge and opportunity grow your skills working on a team of experts. If so, then Security PS is looking for you! Security PS hires capable candidates with a range of experience levels because we believe in investing time to train and develop each person that joins our team into security experts and effective consultants. Security consultants work in a team-oriented environment that values mentoring as well as strong collaboration among peers. Team members in this role participate in activities including:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Application penetration testing  (Web Applications, Thick-Clients, Web Services, Mobile Applications, and more)</li>
	<li>Researching and writing secure coding patterns</li>
	<li>Performing code reviews</li>
</ul>
<p>Team members may also choose to develop security expertise in other areas such as network penetration testing and enterprise security engagements. </p>
<p>Candidates should have a software development background and a passion for security. They are expected to be able to meet project deadlines, follow defined methodology and engagement processes, and work within a team. All consultants interact directly with clients and are responsible for writing detailed documentation, therefore it is imperative that candidates have strong written and verbal communication skills. </p>

<h5 class="media-heading">Summary:</h5>
	<ul>
		<li>Focus: Application Security Testing and Consulting </li>
		<li>Location: Kansas City metro area (local team, virtual office) </li>
		<li>Type: Full Time Employee</li>
		<li>Target Annual Salary: $65k - $95k <i>(dependent on amount of experience and level of training necessary)</i></li>
		<li>Travel Profile: Low travel requirements</li>
		<li>Qualifications Summary:</li>
		<ul>
			<li>Software development experience and experience with a structured software development process</li>
			<li>Solid understanding of application technologies and platforms</li>
			<li>Proficient soft skills (communication, writing, presenting)</li>
			<li>Effective time management, places personal value on hitting deadlines</li>
			<li>Motivated, productive worker, ability to work effectively from home / virtual office environment</li>
			<li>Valuable team member: supports, contributes, collaborates with others well</li>
		</ul>		
		<li>Great Benefits, Including:</li>
		<ul>
			<li>Health/Dental/Vision</li>
			<li>Retirement contribution</li>
			<li>Healthy Living Program</li>
			<li>Paid Time Off program</li>
		</ul>
	</ul>
